      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;bevy-particle-sim&#34;&gt;Bevy particle sim&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/bevyengine/bevy&#34;&gt;Bevy&lt;/a&gt; is a game engine written in Rust that I have taken a bit of a liking to, so &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/PerfectlyInternal/bevy-particle-life&#34;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;&amp;rsquo;s a simple particle physics simulation writted using it. It takes advantage of Bevy&amp;rsquo;s simple and flexible ECS system to efficiently parallelize computations for all the particle interactions.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
